<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-17T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="656" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Brazil/328:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-17T15:00:00-04:00">March 17, 1942—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>671. Your 871 of March 14. Firestone and Goodyear will not continue to
                            act, as Rubber Reserve will deal directly with Bank of Brazil.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>